The story is really good even if its fucked up and characters are very well done.
We can clearly see that miu and kaede have stockholm syndrome towards futaba to cope with trauma she caused them and basically making them addicted, which I would say is somewhat very realistic.
But instead of futaba being your typical unapologetic rapist/abuser she has doubts and struggles about her actions which are sprinkled out during the story.
Story is very well structured and paced and is overall great.
